# Forest Soul Forge — License History

## Active license: Elastic License 2.0 (ELv2)

From commit B245 (2026-05-12) onward, Forest Soul Forge is licensed
under the **Elastic License 2.0**. See the `LICENSE` file for the
full text.

The Licensor is Alexander Price / StellarRequiem.

## Historical license: Apache License 2.0 (commits prior to B245)

All commits up to and including `f799757` (B244 — ADR-0049 tamper-
proof audit chain, 2026-05-12) were released under the **Apache
License 2.0**. Per Apache 2.0 §4, that license is irrevocable for the
specific versions of the Software released under it. Anyone who
received those versions before the relicense retains their Apache 2.0
grants for those versions.

## Why the change

The Apache 2.0 era served the project's bootstrap: maximize integrator
paths during the v0 phase per ADR-0046's original justification. The
ELv2 switch (per ADR-0046 Amendment 2026-05-12) supports the long-
running platform business model the project is building:

- Forest Soul Forge runs as a hosted service.
- Operators can download their agents (hardware-bound at birth per
  ADR-003X K6; cryptographically signed per ADR-0049) to run on their
  own machines.
- The hosted service itself is the commercial offering.

ELv2's three restrictions exactly match this shape:

1. **No competing managed service** — protects the hosted Forge service
   from being commoditized by cloud providers.
2. **No license-key circumvention** — protects subscription / tier
   enforcement when those land.
3. **No notice removal** — protects the project's trademark + author
   attribution.

Use that doesn't violate the three restrictions remains free —
individuals running Forest locally, operators running their downloaded
agents on their own hardware, developers experimenting + studying
the code, etc.

## What this means in practice

| If you... | Then... |
|---|---|
| Forked the repo before 2026-05-12 | Your fork at that point is Apache 2.0; you may continue to use and distribute that snapshot under Apache 2.0 forever. Improvements you sync from upstream after 2026-05-12 carry the ELv2 license. |
| Want to integrate Forest into a closed-source product running on customer hardware | Permitted under ELv2 — the "no competing managed service" restriction only triggers when YOU offer Forest as a hosted service to YOUR customers. |
| Want to offer Forest as a managed service to third parties | Requires a separate commercial license from the Licensor. Contact the project. |
| Are a small developer experimenting with Forest commercially on your own hardware | Permitted under ELv2. |
| Are an enterprise integrator who wants to ship Forest inside an on-prem appliance | Permitted under ELv2 as long as the three restrictions hold; commercial licenses available for accelerated terms. |

For ambiguous cases, the canonical text in `LICENSE` controls. This
file is operator-facing context, not the license itself.

## Future evolution

The ELv2 license has no automatic conversion clause. The Licensor
reserves the right to release future versions of the Software under a
different license (more permissive or otherwise) at the Licensor's
discretion. Any such future change will appear here as a new section.

